The proposed solution is a bit rough (but works and intent is clear).


Alternatively one could add a helper function and replace line 208;
<details>

Helper function: 
```cpp
void TorControlConnection::AppendReplyLine(std::string_view payload)
{
    if (payload.size() > MAX_REPLY_SIZE - m_message.size) {
        throw std::runtime_error(strprintf("Control port reply exceeded %d bytes, disconnecting", MAX_REPLY_SIZE));
    }
    m_message.size += payload.size();
    m_message.lines.emplace_back(payload);
}
```

then replace line 208: 
```cpp
 m_message.lines.push_back(line->substr(4));
```
with the call to the helper function:
```cpp
AppendReplyLine(line->substr(4));
```

(and some changes in the headerfile to add size there. ) 
```cpp
class TorControlReply
{
public:
    TorControlReply() { Clear(); }

    int code;
    size_t size;
    std::vector<std::string> lines;

    void Clear()
    {
        code = 0;
        size = 0;
        lines.clear();
    }
};
```

</details>

